### File Location Rules
- New components must be placed in appropriate directories based on their purpose:
  + Generic UI components в†’ `Components/UI/`
  + Project-specific components в†’ `Components/Project/`
  + Authentication related в†’ `Components/Auth/`
- Pages must follow the route structure in `Pages/` directory
- All API services must be in `services/` directory
- All types must be in `types/` directory
- All hooks must be in `hooks/` directory
- All utilities must be in `utils/` directory

### Code Organization Rules
- Each feature should be self-contained in `features/` directory
- Shared components should be in `Components/UI/`
- Each page should have its own directory if it has multiple sub-components
- Redux store files should be organized by feature
- Types should be separated by domain (models, API, etc.)

### Technology Stack
- Backend:
  + Laravel 12
  + PHP 8.x
  + MySQL/PostgreSQL
  + PHPUnit for testing

- Frontend:
  + React.js
  + Redux for state management
  + TypeScript
  + Inertia.js
  + Vite as build tool
  + TailwindCSS for styling

### Key Components
- UI Components:
  + Buttons (Primary, Secondary, Danger)
  + TextInput, Modal, Dropdown
  + LoadingOverlay, Checkbox
  + Navigation components
  + Form components

- Pages:
  + Welcome
  + Dashboard
  + Auth pages
  + Profile management
  + Sprint management

### Development Features
- Code splitting with dynamic imports
- Environment variables support
- Progress bar for navigation
- TypeScript integration
- Hot module replacement
- Asset bundling with Vite

### Best Practices
- Feature-based code organization
- Reusable UI components
- Custom React hooks
- Type safety with TypeScript
- Consistent layouts
- Secure authentication
- Database transaction management
- Comprehensive testing

